# ADR-001 — Atlas Starts as a New System

## Status

Accepted

## Date

2026-07-01

## Context

An existing Obsidian vault already contains historical notes.

Migrating all legacy content into Atlas would introduce unnecessary complexity, delay adoption, and mix historical structures with a new knowledge system.

## Decision

Atlas starts as a brand-new Obsidian Vault.

No legacy notes will be migrated.

Existing notes remain in the previous vault and may be imported manually only when they become relevant.

## Consequences

### Positive

- Clean information architecture.
- Fast project start.
- No migration burden.
- Atlas evolves from Day 0 with consistent principles.

### Negative

- Historical knowledge is temporarily separated.
- Some useful notes may need manual migration later.
